  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Screen readers:</strong> Will read the content, helping users understand keyboard shortcuts</li>
      <li><strong>Visual distinction:</strong> Key-like styling helps sighted users identify keyboard input</li>
      <li><strong>Plus signs:</strong> Use the plus symbol (+) between keys in combinations for clarity</li>
      <li><strong>Descriptive text:</strong> Provide context around keyboard shortcuts (e.g., "Press X to do Y")</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Best Practices</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Document keyboard shortcuts in a discoverable location</li>
      <li>Provide alternative methods for actions with keyboard shortcuts</li>
      <li>Use consistent terminology for keys (e.g., "Enter" not "Return" for consistency)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

